data.text:
NEW YORK — Jimmy Fallon says he and his wife had their baby daughter with the help of a surrogate. Winnie Rose Fallon, the daughter of the NBC late-night comic and his wife, Nancy Juvonen, was born July 23. Fallon,a Saugerties High School graduate, said in a portion of a “Today” show interview broadcast Friday that the couple had been trying for a while to have a child before succeeding with the help of a surrogate. The couple kept it all a secret until Winnie was born. NBC said a more extensive portion of Savannah Guthrie’s interview with the incoming “The Tonight Show” host will be broadcast next week. Online: http://www.today.com/

Originally Published: August 9, 2013 at 4:44 p.m.
